# Landing Page Visual Overhaul

The current GreenSky Solar landing page uses a flat white/slate design with basic cards. The goal is to make it visually **powerful and premium** — adding depth, richer gradients, micro-animations, a dark-mode-inspired hero, glassmorphism, and more dynamic interactions without changing the page's content or business logic.

## Proposed Changes

### Global Styles

#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/app/globals.css)
- Add CSS custom properties for glow effects and gradient utilities
- Add keyframe animations for floating particles, shimmer effects, and subtle pulsing glows
- Add a gradient text utility class for section headings

---

### Hero & Page Sections

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/app/page.tsx)

**Bug fix:** Remove the duplicate Services section (lines 311–340 are an exact copy of lines 282–310).

**Hero Carousel:**
- Add animated floating particles/orbs behind the overlay for a dynamic, alive feel
- Add a subtle gradient shimmer to the headline text
- Add a glowing pulsing accent ring on the "Book Now" CTA button
- Improve the gradient overlay (deeper, richer, more cinematic)
- Add a scroll-down indicator at the bottom of the hero

**Stats Section:**
- Replace flat white cards with glassmorphic cards (translucent background, backdrop-blur, subtle border glow)
- Add gradient background behind the entire stats strip (dark green → emerald gradient)
- Animate stat icons with a subtle glow pulse
- Make the stat numbers glow green on count-up

**About Section:**
- Add a decorative gradient orb behind the text for depth
- Add a thin accent divider with a gradient line between heading and body text
- Add a subtle animated leaf/sparkle icon accent

**Services Section:**
- Redesign cards with gradient borders on hover (green-to-teal shimmer)
- Add a subtle inner glow on the icon container
- Stagger card entrance animations
- Add a "Starting from ₱XX" price tag badge on each card (data already exists in constants)

**Why Choose Us Section:**
- Switch to a dark slate/charcoal background for contrast
- Use glassmorphic cards with green glow borders
- Add a large decorative gradient blur behind the section
- Add animated number highlights

**CTA Section:**
- Add animated radial gradient pulses in the background
- Add floating particle dots
- Add a glowing ring animation on the CTA button

---

### Testimonials

#### [MODIFY] [TestimonialsSection.tsx](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/components/landing/TestimonialsSection.tsx)
- Switch background to a dark gradient (slate-900 → slate-800)
- Make the testimonial card glassmorphic with a green accent glow
- Add a star rating display (5 stars) for each testimonial
- Add avatar initials circles with gradient backgrounds
- Larger, more prominent quote icon with glow effect

---

### Header

#### [MODIFY] [LandingHeader.tsx](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/components/layout/LandingHeader.tsx)
- Add a green glow/shadow to the "Log In" button on hover
- Add a gradient underline effect on nav link hover (instead of solid brand color)

---

### New Component

#### [NEW] [FloatingParticles.tsx](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/components/landing/FloatingParticles.tsx)
- Animated floating gradient orbs/dots that drift upward
- Uses Framer Motion for smooth continuous animations
- Reusable across hero and CTA sections

## Verification Plan

### Browser Verification
- Run `npm run dev` and open the landing page in a browser
- Visually verify each section has the new premium styling: hero particles, glassmorphic stats, gradient accents, dark testimonials section, improved CTA
- Verify the duplicate Services section bug is fixed
- Check responsive behavior on mobile viewport (375px) and desktop (1440px)
- Verify all hover effects and animations work smoothly
- Verify page still builds without errors via `npm run build`

> [!NOTE]
> Existing tests ([auth.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/lib/auth.test.ts), [format.test.ts](file:///c:/Users/rodne/Desktop/anada%20wan/greensky-solar/src/lib/format.test.ts)) cover unrelated utility logic — no landing page tests exist, and visual redesign is best verified via browser inspection rather than unit tests.
